# Noosphere Steward — ALWAYS EXPLICIT

This project uses the Noosphere Steward rule system. Source of truth: `assets/Noosphere Steward/`.

**Hard rule:** Steward is never implicit. Every agent response includes a visible **STEWARD PASS** block (see below). If steward files were not read this turn, say so in that block — do not pretend bootstrap ran.

User directive (2026-06-24): **explicit Noosphere ALWAYS.**

---

## STEWARD PASS — mandatory in every response

Include this block at the start of every reply (after any brief lead-in, before the main answer). Use a **markdown table** — not an ASCII tree. Cursor chat soft-wraps monospace trees and breaks them; tables survive wrap per row.

**Trivial requests only** (typo fix, single rename, yes/no factual lookup with no design/code impact):

**STEWARD PASS — trivial; bootstrap skipped**

All other requests — full block (copy this shape; fill values only):

**STEWARD PASS**

| | |
|---|---|
| Ground | one line from USER.md intent |
| Read | steward files read this turn (or none — prior context + which) |
| Ambiguity | Low \| Medium \| High |
| Anchors | entry modules / files in scope |
| Bridges | data flows or design deps traced |
| Blast | what breaks if the proposed direction is wrong |
| Invariants | state \| feedback \| delete \| timing (one line, or n/a) |
| Baseline | one anchored proposal — not an open option cloud |
| Curvature | what the user can accept / reject / recurse on |

### STEWARD PASS layout — hard rules

1. **Markdown table only** — no `├──` / `└──` trees, no code fences around the live block.
2. **Title then table** — bold `**STEWARD PASS**`, blank line, then the 2-column table. Trivial pass is one bold line, no table.
3. **Exactly 9 rows** — Ground, Read, Ambiguity, Anchors, Bridges, Blast, Invariants, Baseline, Curvature (fixed labels, column 1).
4. **One row per field** — entire value in column 2; never split a field across rows.
5. **Invariants** — four segments in one cell, separated by ` \| `.
6. **Long values** — OK if the cell wraps; keep terse anyway.

**Never:**
- Skip STEWARD PASS because the task "feels simple"
- Offer multiple peer options without naming a baseline first
- Guess UI pixels, feel, or copy (USER holds that truth; flag for Figma/user)
- Write or modify code without tracing invariants on Medium+ ambiguity

**Always:**
- Propose one baseline; user accepts, rejects, or recurses ([AGENTS.md](assets/Noosphere Steward/AGENTS.md) friction loop)
- Surface tension in prose — do not internalize ambiguity
- Map before you cross on any code or multi-module design work

