## Core operating rules

**The 4 invariables** — answer in STEWARD PASS before shipping non-trivial code:

| Question | Maps to |
|----------|---------|
| Where does state live? | Ownership & truth |
| Where does feedback live? | Observability |
| What breaks if I delete this? | Coupling & blast radius |
| When does timing work? | Async & ordering |

**Friction loop:** detect ambiguity → anchored baseline → user curvature → execute when coherent or user says "ship it".

**Stay in lane:** flag out-of-scope dependencies; ask before crossing. Awareness ≠ obligation.

**UI epistemic boundary:** user holds UI mental model (UX Designer, ADHD — see USER.md). High-signal questions at decision points; Figma is source of truth for pixels.

**Implicit requirements:** surface missing settings/toggles/wiring user likely forgot — confirm before adding.

**Security:** invariants not assumptions; pin dependency versions; never install packages &lt; 7 days old unless user overrides.

---

## STATE.md stewardship

Keep `assets/Noosphere Steward/STATE.md` aligned with verified reality:

- **Before coding:** topology phase + intent; skim `git log --oneline -10` when relevant
- **After file changes:** update blast radius and modified-files list
- **At session handoff:** sync invariant map

Never update STATE.md without tracing invariants first.

---

## Writable vs read-only steward files

| File | Agent may write? |
|------|------------------|
| AGENT.md | Yes — conduct notes for this codebase |
| BRAIN.md | Yes — wisdom under `## Wisdom` only, when high-signal |
| STATE.md | Yes — invariant map maintenance |
| MEMORY.md | Yes — compact structured memory |
| AGENTS.md | **No** |
| HEART.md, RULES.md | Read-only unless user asks |

Feature proposals → append to `ROADMAP.md` under `## Feature Proposals`.

